  "prompt": "What is the best way to fumigate a mattress?",
  "response": "Here are some effective methods to fumigate a mattress:\n\n1. Steam cleaning\n- Kills dust mites and bacteria\n- Uses high-temperature steam\n- Effective and chemical-free\n\n2. Sunlight exposure\n- Natural disinfection method\n- Place mattress in direct sunlight for several hours\n- Helps kill dust mites and bacteria\n\n3. Professional mattress cleaning\n- Most thorough method\n- Uses specialized equipment and treatments\n- Recommended for severe infestations\n\n4. Diatomaceous earth\n- Natural, non-toxic powder\n- Sprinkle over mattress surface\n- Leave for several hours, then vacuum thoroughly\n- Kills dust mites and bed bugs\n\n5. Alcohol and vinegar spray\n- Mix equal parts water and white vinegar\n- Add rubbing alcohol\n- Spray lightly on mattress surface\n- Allow to dry completely\n\n6. Baking soda treatment\n- Sprinkle baking soda over mattress\n- Let sit for several hours\n- Vacuum thoroughly\n- Helps neutralize odors and kill some bacteria\n\n7. Commercial mattress sanitizing sprays\n- Available at most stores\n- Follow manufacturer's instructions carefully\n\nAlways ensure the mattress is completely dry before using to prevent mold growth.",
